At least three people, including a motorist and two hijackers, were killed in the shooting on Saturday. CAPE TOWN - Officials say a policeman wounded during a deadly shoot-out on Main Reef Road in Riverlea, south-west of Johannesburg, is recovering well in hospital and is hoping to be discharged soon.At least three people, including a motorist and two hijackers, were killed in the shooting on Saturday.It s understood around nine men faced off with police after they were spotted driving in a hijacked minibus.Two of the suspects were killed while the others fled on foot.Police s Kay Makhubela said, Finding the rifles in their possessions is a sign that those criminals were prepared to fight and terrorise our community. We want to applaud the flying squads from Soweto and Johannesburg and the Johannesburg central police who actually identified these suspects ad gave chase to them. 